main event: An unidentified object was sighted and later concluded to be Venus by military officials.
interesting points: The object was described as the size of a quarter and white in color, traveling South to West in a straight level movement., The object's altitude was estimated to be over 20,000 feet., Observers at Biggs AFB dispatched jet fighters to investigate the object., The investigation determined that the object was mechanically traveling at a speed over 1200 MPH., Further investigation was discontinued once it was identified as Venus.
sighted object: a round disc with a bright light in the center
